SIMPLE: controlment
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Controlment
<hw>Con*trol"ment</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
power or act of controlling; the state of being restrained; control;
restraint; regulation; superintendence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>You may do it without <qex>controlment</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Opposition; resistance; hostility.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Here have we war for war, and blood for blood,⟦br⟧
<qex>Controlment</qex> for controlment.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Control theory</ent>⟦br⟧
